$interpreted: Crushfang: Have there been any changes since the last time humans invaded?
Strict Bear Elder: Seems like there's more of them this time.
Impulsive Bear Elder: I hear fighting! Over there!
Dagger: Damn humans!
Illegal Miner Foreman: Kill him!
Crushfang: Dagger, look out!
Dagger: I don't need a weakling like you looking out for me!
Crushfang: Listen, I hate humans as much as you do, but I can't allow more bears to die in a pointless war.
Dagger: Whole lot of good you've done so far! My father's dead because of you!
Dagger: You have no right to lead the bears!
Impulsive Bear Elder: Chieftain, is something bothering you?

Crushfang: I feel as if I've seen one of those miners before... 
Inform me immediately if the same group shows up again.
Crushfang: Did Dagger really just say that?
Strict Bear Elder: Yes. Perhaps the chieftain has too strict on him in the past.
Crushfang: Can't take a bit of scolding, what kind of bear is he?
Strict Bear Elder: He is indeed still a cub... one with no parents, nonetheless.
Crushfang: Does that mean I should go easy on him?
Strict Bear Elder: No, but sometimes, kind words work better than harsh scolding.
Crushfang: Kind words...
Dumb Bear Soldier: ...*growl*...*growl*...
Furygrowl: ......*growl*.......
Crushfang: Dagger, I need to talk with you. Stay right there!
Crushfang: Was that the correct attitude when addressing your elders?
Dagger: ......
Crushfang: Your Rite of Passage is just around the corner. You need to grow up.
Dagger: ......
Crushfang: If your father saw you like this...
Dagger: Shut up! You have no right to talk about him!
